1
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:13,440
<i>Song is someone I want to date,</i>

2
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:15,960
<i>marry, and build a family with.</i>

3
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:17,480
<i>I don't feel anything for you.</i>

4
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,600
<i>I want to open a matcha café.</i>

5
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,120
<i>I'll handle the location</i>

6
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,680
<i>and the shop decoration too.</i>

7
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:23,880
<i>Ple, kiss me.</i>

8
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:25,520
<i>Make that woman jealous.</i>

9
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,800
<i>Kissing? I think that's a bit too much.</i>

10
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:29,600
I've done this with lots of people.

11
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:31,960
<i>Even if you kiss another woman,</i>

12
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:34,320
<i>it won't make me like you any less.</i>

13
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:37,800
<i>So where are we going?</i>

14
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:38,920
<i>To a hotel.</i>

15
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:51,480
Sleep here.

16
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:54,760
Drink some warm
lemon water in the morning.

17
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:57,200
I'll ask room service
to prepare it for you.

18
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:02,600
Wait.

19
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,920
Song, where are you going?

20
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,040
Are you leaving me here alone?

21
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:13,640
It's safe here.

22
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,480
No one is going to hurt you.

23
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:19,240
How can you be so sure?

24
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:20,520
When we came up earlier,

25
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:23,400
there was this guy staring
at me so creepily.

26
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:27,600
What if you leave and he comes after me?

27
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:32,800
Why do you remember
every detail so clearly?

28
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:34,120
Are you sober already?

29
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:38,080
I was never drunk in the first place.

30
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,960
Ten shots of water, please.

31
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,080
Excuse me?

32
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,920
Ten shots of water, please.

33
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,080
Hurry up, I'm super thirsty.

34
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,360
Please wait a moment.

35
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:58,120
And some lime too, my throat hurts.

36
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,240
Sure thing.

37
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,720
Here you go, ten shots of water.

38
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,560
- Here's lime.
- Thank you.

39
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,560
So you were just acting?

40
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:14,600
Yeah, though I don't think
I acted that well.

41
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:17,600
Because if I were really drunk,
you would've smelled it.

42
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:20,960
You're pretty easy to fool, you know.

43
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:22,760
What do you want?

44
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:25,000
Why are you playing with my feelings?

45
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,920
Feelings?

46
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,000
What kind of feelings?

47
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,600
Hold up, Song.

48
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:38,120
I didn't mean to trick you.

49
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,640
I just wanted a chance to be close to you.

50
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:42,440
And…

51
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:45,480
I wanted payback
for you kissing your friend.

52
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:48,360
I know you and that girl are just friends.

53
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:50,440
And you kissed in front of me on purpose.

54
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,160
Just to make me give up on you.

55
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,480
But let me tell you this.

56
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,840
I'll never give up on you.

57
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:57,600
I'll do anything.

58
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,360
To win your heart.

59
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,120
And I've already started.

60
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:07,320
So you dressing like this,

61
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,560
trying to act more mature,

62
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:12,160
and trying to build something
for yourself…

63
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,080
Yes.

64
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,560
So it didn't work at all?

65
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:22,920
Then… what about this?

66
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:04,440
Get away from me.

67
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:09,680
Why?

68
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:14,680
Are you scared
that if we sleep together again,

69
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,680
you'll fall for me even more?

70
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,040
No.

71
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:22,640
I'm scared you won't be able to handle it.

72
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:26,800
One reason I never see anyone twice

73
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:30,120
is because I know the second time

74
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:32,640
will definitely be more intense
than the first.

75
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:38,360
And you think I'll be scared?

76
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:40,040
Don't challenge me.

77
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:44,960
If I get serious,
don't say I didn't warn you.

78
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,920
I warned you, Piang.

79
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,920
When you call my name,

80
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,240
it's really sexy.

81
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:53,760
No matter how intense this gets,
I'm not stopping.

82
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,000
You said it.

83
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:59,120
If you can't get out of bed tomorrow,

84
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,200
don't blame me.

85
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,120
Thanks

86
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,600
for taking me home.

87
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:48,040
Are you sure you want me
to drop you off here?

88
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,920
I'm not that drunk.

89
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,360
And besides,

90
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:55,440
I don't like people getting involved in
my personal space either.

91
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:57,920
Letting you take me this far
is already more than enough.

92
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,440
Why are you smiling?

93
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:09,200
Well, the way you said that
makes me feel like I'm someone special.

94
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,920
Nonsense.

95
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:15,720
It's just that you already promised Song,

96
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,600
so I didn't want to say no.

97
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:21,360
- It doesn't mean anything.
- Okay, okay.

98
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:24,240
If you say so. Then I'm heading home.

99
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:48,600
Ple. Do you remember me?

100
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,680
We matched on a dating app.

101
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:53,920
You live here?

102
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:01,160
Why are you in such a hurry?

103
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:05,000
Hey. The room is boring.

104
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:08,040
Let's go have some fun in the car instead.

105
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:10,240
Why would I?

106
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,520
Hey.

107
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,280
We're not kids anymore.

108
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:19,000
You should know why I'm asking.

109
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:23,760
My rule is one time only, no repeats.

110
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:24,920
Got it?

111
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,000
Hey, stop playing hard to get.

112
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,120
Just one round, come on.

113
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,080
- Come on, it'll be quick.
- No.

114
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:33,000
- Hey.
- Or maybe right here?

115
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,440
- Right here works too.
- Don't.

116
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:35,680
- Let go.
- Come on.

117
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:37,400
Let go.

118
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,960
If she said no, then it's over, isn't it?

119
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,640
If you're that desperate, go pay for it.

120
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:44,440
Or are you too broke for that?

121
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:45,520
Who the hell are you?

122
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,320
- And who are you?
- Why do you care?

123
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,680
I do care. Got a problem? Then come at me.

124
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,720
You think being a woman
means I won't do shit?

125
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,920
- Bring it on.
- Come on then, come here.

126
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,720
- Come at me.
- Come on.

127
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,960
Come at me.

128
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:58,120
- Hit me first.
- Fine.

129
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,840
With a disgusting face like yours,

130
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:01,720
I'm definitely posting this
on social media.

131
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:02,840
Go ahead.

132
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:06,120
Think you're tough? Come on then.

133
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:09,080
What the hell are you filming?

134
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,040
So what, you twig-looking moron?

135
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:13,480
- You're the moron.
- You're the moron. Just go home.

136
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,000
You shameless asshole.
She already rejected you.

137
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,720
Are you hurt?

138
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:33,880
No.

139
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:39,080
Just say it if you are. Why act tough?

140
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:48,160
Let me come up to your room.

141
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,840
Let me treat that for you.

142
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:05,160
Can I consider myself special now?

143
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:07,240
You're even letting me into your room.

144
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:11,160
Relax.

145
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:13,000
I was just teasing you.

146
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:17,040
Do you feel better now?

147
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,600
Yeah, a little.

148
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:21,400
I mean your arm.

149
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,160
And your heart too.

150
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:26,320
I saw when he grabbed you.

151
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:28,160
You didn't look okay at all.

152
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,200
Just a little.

153
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,920
What he did…

154
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:38,400
reminded me of the worst time in my life.

155
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:41,440
So what if I have someone else?

156
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:43,120
Did you ever think about me?

157
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:45,360
- What about us?
- Did you just insult me?

158
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:49,440
Your job is to endure it, understand?

159
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,160
You're a shitty husband!

160
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,880
- You bastard, you piece of shit!
- It's my own damn business!

161
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,400
What about it?

162
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,480
Asshole!

163
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,920
It's my own damn business!

164
00:12:05,680 --> 00:12:06,840
You bastard!

165
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,680
But whatever. You should go home now.

166
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:14,080
I want to rest.

167
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:15,960
Okay.

168
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:17,720
But if he bothers you again,

169
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:19,760
you have to tell me, okay?

170
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:22,440
I'll drag his ass
through social media justice.

171
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:25,040
And make him face a real court too.

172
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:27,600
He's definitely getting charged
with sexual harassment.

173
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:29,960
You dog-faced piece of shit.

174
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,240
What kind of insult is that?

175
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,680
He's ugly.
And his personality was even worse.

176
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:41,800
Next time you pick someone,
choose better, okay?

177
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:44,080
Okay.

178
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:46,520
You sure nag a lot. You should go now.

179
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,160
Okay.

180
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:54,720
Don't forget.

181
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,720
If anything happens, tell me.

182
00:12:58,520 --> 00:12:59,720
I know.

183
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,680
Good.

184
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,360
I'm going now.

185
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:13,320
She keeps saying
to tell her if anything happens.

186
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,840
But how am I supposed to do that?

187
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:36,840
Crazy kid.

188
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,280
Wake up.

189
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:12,960
Wake up already.

190
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:26,640
Song, are you okay?

191
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:30,320
Why is your face so red
and you're sweating so much?

192
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:52,080
I'm fine.

193
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:55,120
I just went for a run.

194
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:03,120
Still full of energy?

195
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:06,120
Even though we just did it last night…

196
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:09,600
It's something I have to do every day.
If I don't want to take medicine.

197
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,720
What medicine?

198
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:19,400
Stop asking so many questions.

199
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:25,360
Take this.
I stopped by to buy these for you.

200
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:29,440
Hangover drinks and…

201
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:38,040
A T-shirt?

202
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:40,640
Yeah. Your shirt got ripped yesterday.

203
00:16:43,760 --> 00:16:46,640
I was the one who did it.
So I should take responsibility.

204
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:52,640
Go take a shower.
It's really late already.

205
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:55,640
How late is really late?

206
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:58,400
- Seven thirty.
- Seven thirty?

207
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:05,400
Nope. Get up right now.

208
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:07,640
Let me sleep a little longer.

209
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:09,240
Get up.

210
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:17,720
What's wrong?

211
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,880
My stomach hurts.

212
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:26,040
Was I too rough last night?

213
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,360
Yeah.

214
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:32,160
Honestly, it's been hurting
since last night.

215
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,680
But I didn't want to interrupt.

216
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:39,360
I've invested this much for you.

217
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,320
You have to date me now.

218
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,440
Ridiculous.

219
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,680
Go shower already.

220
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:53,600
Fine, I'm going.

221
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:02,000
I wonder if anyone wants
to shower with me?

222
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:11,960
Didn't I tell you
to take good care of your sister?

223
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:14,640
Then why did you let her
disappear all night?

224
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,920
Well…

225
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:22,840
You two are hiding something
from me, aren't you?

226
00:18:23,360 --> 00:18:25,840
No, that's not it, Grandma. It's just…

227
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:28,160
I tried calling her last night,

228
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,920
but her phone probably died, Grandma.

229
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,280
Please don't scold her, Grandma.

230
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:34,120
You're back already?

231
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,360
Where the hell were you all night?

232
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:40,240
I went drinking with Mon.

233
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:42,520
Then I stayed over at her place.

234
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:45,880
I'm sorry, Mudmee,
for not telling you first and…

235
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:47,960
I'm sorry too, Grandma,
for making you worry.

236
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:52,520
Piang. Since you were little,

237
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:55,680
has there ever been a time you lied
and I didn't catch you?

238
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:58,280
You know how strong my instincts are.

239
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:02,640
Maybe your instincts
are getting weaker with age.

240
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:04,560
- Piang.
- What did you say?

241
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:07,200
I'll head upstairs first.

242
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,400
Mudmee, come with me.

243
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,680
I want to discuss Sensu Garden
with you too.

244
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:15,680
Grandma. I'm building my own café.

245
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:19,480
I'll prove to you that this granddaughter
you think is useless

246
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:21,120
is capable too.

247
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:23,520
And one day, when I can stand on my own,

248
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:25,440
I'll choose for myself.

249
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:28,200
Choose what?

250
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:30,800
The person I'll marry and have kids with.

251
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:32,760
I'll choose for myself.

252
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:34,880
Whether you approve or not.

253
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:36,640
Let's go.

254
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:52,760
Piang. You didn't really sleep
at Mon's place last night, did you?

255
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:59,080
No, I was with Song.

256
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:06,760
Now I'm starting to wonder
if helping you was the right choice.

257
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:09,200
Mudmee, I'm sorry. It's just…

258
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:12,640
A lot of things happened last night.

259
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:13,680
No time to tell you.

260
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:17,320
I promise from now on
I'll tell you everything.

261
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:30,240
What were you thinking,
blurting out to Grandma

262
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:32,000
that you'd choose your own life partner?

263
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:34,440
Saying that only made
Grandma more suspicious.

264
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:37,040
And I'm absolutely sure

265
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:39,240
Grandma's going to
have someone investigate.

266
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:41,280
Then she'll definitely find out the truth.

267
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:44,120
I don't even want to imagine

268
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,640
what it'll be like.

269
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:51,840
What's wrong? Does your stomach hurt?

270
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:55,800
It hurts. Song was too rough
with me last night…

271
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,480
Stop talking.

272
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:03,200
Why should I? I already promised
to tell you everything.

273
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:04,840
Forget the promise.

274
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:07,960
Just tell me…
the things you actually should.

275
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,240
Understand?

276
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,880
Go find some medicine.

277
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:25,680
She's so insatiable.

278
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:40,640
<i>What's wrong?</i>

279
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:42,120
My stomach hurts.

280
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:46,360
Actually, it's been hurting
since last night.

281
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:48,800
But I didn't want to interrupt.

282
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,200
Here.

283
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:15,520
THE FOOD IS DELICIOUS,
BUT THE CHEF LOOKS EVEN TASTIER

284
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:36,160
Who is it? Can't you see
my stomach hurts right now?

285
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:39,320
If this isn't important,
I'm gonna tear you apart.

286
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:41,920
<i>It's me.</i>

287
00:22:49,120 --> 00:22:50,600
Pi Song.

288
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:12,120
<i>Who is this?</i>

289
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,520
She's gone now.

290
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,360
<i>Are you Song?</i>

291
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:31,640
<i>You already know that.</i>

292
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:35,120
You're no fun at all.

293
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:38,200
<i>Did you text me for a reason?</i>

294
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,800
<i>How's the pain now?</i>

295
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:44,680
So you were worried about me after all.

296
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,840
It hurt earlier,

297
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:53,120
but the moment you texted me,
it went away.

298
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:55,400
Thank you for worrying about me.

299
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:00,920
<i>It hurt earlier,</i>

300
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,640
<i>but the moment you texted me,</i>
<i>it went away.</i>

301
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:05,800
<i>Thank you for worrying about me.</i>

302
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:09,880
Bring her around to meet me sometime.

303
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:11,320
What?

304
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:14,640
The person who said you care about her.

305
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:16,560
I want to meet her.

306
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:19,000
There isn't anyone, Grandma.

307
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:24,160
Song, people's thoughts
can change all the time.

308
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:27,280
And life is very short.

309
00:24:27,360 --> 00:24:30,080
So we shouldn't waste our lives

310
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:32,160
being stuck in the past.

311
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:34,360
And there's no need to worry

312
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:37,760
about a future that hasn't arrived yet.

313
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:39,240
Most importantly, my dear,

314
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:41,680
people need to live in the present.

315
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:45,400
And if something brings us
joy and happiness,

316
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:47,600
we should embrace it.

317
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:51,520
And never let it go easily, understand?

318
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,880
I told you, there isn't anyone.

319
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:58,520
There isn't, huh? If you say so.

320
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,920
By the way,
what's that person's name again?

321
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,640
Grandma.

322
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:10,040
Sure, whatever you say.
"I'm worried about you."

323
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:12,440
"I miss you so much." I want to meet them.

324
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:15,040
I want to meet her so badly.

325
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:21,320
Moo Grob.

326
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:24,760
It's been so long since I last saw you.

327
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:31,600
Finally back with Mommy again.

328
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:34,560
I missed you so much.

329
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:46,280
Looks like Song
really is getting better now.

330
00:25:46,360 --> 00:25:49,720
Neung, make sure you support
your sister too, dear.

331
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:13,960
Sorry I'm late.

332
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:17,040
I had some work
I needed to clear up first.

333
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:18,840
Please, sit.

334
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,720
You're not the type
to work on weekends, Mr. Sarut.

335
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:28,120
Maybe that was true before.

336
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:33,760
But lately, I've heard
you've been living at the golf course.

337
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:35,120
Well,

338
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:39,760
they say you can know everything
without going to the company.

339
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,400
That must be true.

340
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,640
Let's get to the point.

341
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:46,640
Piang has been going
to the company a lot lately.

342
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:48,520
Is there something I should know?

343
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:52,320
Actually, I was just about
to talk to you about that.

344
00:26:59,440 --> 00:27:00,400
Here.

345
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:03,640
This woman's name is Sadanun.

346
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:06,320
She's the best researcher
who stole the position from me.

347
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:09,240
The reason Piang keeps going
to the company

348
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:10,720
is because she's seeing her.

349
00:27:12,560 --> 00:27:15,880
I've had my people keep an eye on them
and collect evidence.

350
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:19,000
I'm worried that Piang is being deceived.

351
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,320
Being deceived?

352
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,840
Why would you think that?

353
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:29,440
That woman has worked
at the company for four or five years,

354
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:32,160
but she's kept her personal life
completely hidden.

355
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:34,240
No one knows who she really is.

356
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:36,680
And the information
in her records is practically blank.

357
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:40,680
But she seems unusually determined
to get close to Piang.

358
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:43,240
Piang is still very young.

359
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:46,320
I'm worried she'll fall
for that woman's tricks.

360
00:27:52,280 --> 00:27:53,600
You said…

361
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:57,600
this woman took the position
from you, right?

362
00:27:58,720 --> 00:27:59,520
Yes.

363
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:02,720
Then how can I trust
that everything you're saying

364
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:05,200
isn't just because of jealousy or revenge?

365
00:28:05,960 --> 00:28:09,440
Come on. I'm not that kind of person.

366
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:12,320
You know very well
that everyone knows who Piang is

367
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:14,000
and what benefits come with her.

368
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:18,280
Do you really think
that woman truly loves Piang?

369
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:46,480
<i>I won't be seeing you today.</i>

370
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:48,360
<i>Going to check on the café's progress.</i>

371
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:55,880
<i>That's your business.</i>

372
00:29:03,040 --> 00:29:04,160
<i>It's our business.</i>

373
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:06,120
<i>This café only exists because of you.</i>

374
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:12,920
<i>Work hard, my talented girl. Mwah.</i>

375
00:29:25,040 --> 00:29:27,320
Why are you smiling, Song?

376
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:30,480
I'm not.

377
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:36,480
You don't have to hide it from me.
I'm fully supporting you, you know.

378
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:38,400
But…

379
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:41,160
you have to support me too.

380
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:44,760
Support you with what?

381
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:49,800
I like Ple.

382
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:00,360
Then prepare to get your heart broken.

383
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:02,440
She's just like me.

384
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:04,560
She doesn't open her heart easily.

385
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,480
Actually, I'm like Piang too.

386
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:12,600
I'm not someone
who gives up easily either.

387
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,240
What do you think?

388
00:30:24,880 --> 00:30:27,120
Can you tell me something?

389
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:29,760
The worst time in Ple's life
that she talked about,

390
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:31,320
when was it?

391
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,160
What happened back then?

392
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:38,720
Please, Song.

393
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:48,760
Ple grew up with a cheating father
who abused her mother.

394
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:52,200
And at some point,

395
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:54,760
both of them chose to abandon her.

396
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:57,480
Since that day,

397
00:30:57,560 --> 00:31:00,960
she stopped believing
that beautiful love could really exist.

398
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:09,240
I understand now.

399
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:14,600
It's actually good that I know this.
Now I know what I should do next.

400
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:17,360
What do you mean by that?

401
00:31:18,120 --> 00:31:20,400
I'm going to make Ple feel better.

402
00:31:23,200 --> 00:31:24,640
Thank you, Song.

403
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:37,040
Hello, Madam.

404
00:31:38,520 --> 00:31:42,040
I have something I need to discuss
with you in private.

405
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:13,840
What are you doing?
And where the hell is Song?

406
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:18,000
The chairwoman is here.

407
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:22,680
Let's hide.

408
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,640
What business do you have with me, Madam?

409
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:33,560
Your name is Song, right?

410
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:34,720
Yes.

411
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:37,520
The company's best researcher.

412
00:32:38,840 --> 00:32:40,160
Yes.

413
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:45,040
Warakij.

414
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:53,520
I've never heard that surname before.

415
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,640
You must come from an ordinary family.

416
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,880
One with no status in high society.

417
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:03,000
Madam, what exactly are you trying to say?

418
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:06,200
Stop seeing my granddaughter.

419
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:09,160
You have nothing worthy of her.

420
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:11,680
- Holy shit.
- Holy shit.

421
00:33:13,760 --> 00:33:18,240
Piang deserves someone
from the same social class.

422
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:21,520
Someone from a family of equal standing.

423
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:23,520
With honor, dignity, and wealth.

424
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:26,160
Someone who can truly support her.

425
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:29,960
Not someone who keeps
their head down working endlessly,

426
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:32,320
waiting for a salary worth less than…

427
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:38,200
…one of her shoes.

428
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:49,520
Thank you for informing me

429
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,680
just how lowly and worthless I am.

430
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:54,080
But honestly,

431
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:57,880
I think you're trying
to solve the wrong problem.

432
00:33:58,440 --> 00:34:01,880
Instead of telling me to stay away
from your granddaughter,

433
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:04,320
you should go tell
your granddaughter instead.

434
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:07,360
Because I've never been
interested in her at all.

435
00:34:07,440 --> 00:34:10,199
She's the one who keeps chasing
after me nonstop.

436
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:11,480
She won't leave.

437
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:15,400
Even if my value is only equal
to the price of one of her shoes,

438
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:21,040
it still seems like
she really wants "this shoe."

439
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:24,320
That was harsh.

440
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:26,560
That was really harsh.

441
00:34:26,639 --> 00:34:29,080
You're very brave
to speak to me like that.

442
00:34:29,159 --> 00:34:30,880
I'm just telling the truth.

443
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:32,560
So I don't need any bravery at all.

444
00:34:32,639 --> 00:34:35,760
Excuse me. I need to get back to work.

445
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:51,679
Song, you…

446
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,000
Let her go.

447
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:54,760
I've seen her furious before.

448
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:58,600
If you keep bothering her,
she'll explode for real.

449
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:09,440
Today I went to see that woman named Song.

450
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:11,240
What?

451
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:18,360
Is it true, as she said, you're the one
chasing after her

452
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:20,120
and bothering her nonstop?

453
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:22,880
Yes.

454
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:24,320
Piang.

455
00:35:25,720 --> 00:35:29,080
I never thought my granddaughter
could behave this pathetically.

456
00:35:29,160 --> 00:35:32,720
Give up on her.
And go date someone I choose for you.

457
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:35,040
Here.

458
00:35:35,920 --> 00:35:37,240
Dr. Namking.

459
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:39,920
She's the granddaughter
of my close friend.

460
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:41,760
I've already chosen this one for you.

461
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,720
She's suitable for you in every way.

462
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:46,480
No.

463
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:49,400
I won't date anyone except Song.

464
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:53,560
Do you really like her that much?

465
00:35:53,640 --> 00:35:54,960
Wow.

466
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:57,640
I wish you could've heard
what she said about you today.

467
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:59,040
She looked down on you.

468
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:02,760
She said you're like a dog
constantly following behind her.

469
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:06,520
Even though she has nothing
that could ever compare to you.

470
00:36:06,600 --> 00:36:08,480
She was just saying that, Grandma.

471
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:10,360
She never says what she means.

472
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:13,560
Next time, if you don't want to hear it,
then don't go talk to her again.

473
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:15,320
Piang.

474
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:22,240
When I told you to go on that date,

475
00:36:22,320 --> 00:36:23,800
it was an order.

476
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:24,760
Not a request.

477
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:28,400
So you will follow my order.

478
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:35,360
Fine. Then I'll go.

479
00:36:36,120 --> 00:36:39,160
But prepare yourself.
Because there's no way I'll ever like her.

480
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:41,760
And if she ends up liking me,

481
00:36:41,840 --> 00:36:44,680
then she'll get heartbroken
and you'll lose a friend.

482
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:47,120
If that's the trade you want,
then fine, I'll do it.

483
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,360
Don't threaten me.

484
00:36:50,440 --> 00:36:56,000
I'll do anything
to keep you away from that woman.

485
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:27,040
<i>Song. I heard about</i>
<i>my grandma talking to you.</i>

486
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:30,240
<i>No matter what she said,</i>
<i>don't take it to heart.</i>

487
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:32,080
<i>And absolutely don't waver, okay?</i>

488
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:44,160
<i>You read it, so reply to me already.</i>

489
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:46,120
<i>I've been waiting</i>
<i>for your message all day.</i>

490
00:37:51,400 --> 00:37:52,480
<i>I'm busy working.</i>

491
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:03,000
<i>I wish you'd be attached to me</i>
<i>the same way you're attached to work.</i>

492
00:38:10,640 --> 00:38:12,560
Boss, is there anything I can help with?

493
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:16,760
Well… I came to apologize
on behalf of my grandma.

494
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:19,920
I don't know what exactly she said to you,

495
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:23,040
but if she said anything hurtful,

496
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:24,520
please don't take it personally.

497
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:27,240
Grandma really loves Piang a lot,

498
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:29,360
so she may have a few too many conditions.

499
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:31,680
I understand.

500
00:38:31,760 --> 00:38:33,840
At first I was upset too,

501
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:36,760
but after thinking about it,
I don't feel anything anymore.

502
00:38:36,840 --> 00:38:38,320
And more importantly,

503
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,960
I also said some things back to her too.

504
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:45,960
So I should apologize to you, too.

505
00:38:47,520 --> 00:38:50,160
Now that's more like you.

506
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:53,760
By the way, why aren't you home yet?

507
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:55,240
Or are you still finishing work?

508
00:38:56,680 --> 00:38:58,960
Actually, the project we're
presenting tomorrow

509
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:00,920
still needs more information added.

510
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:05,600
I'm here for you.

511
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:07,880
If Team B can get through this project,

512
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:09,440
you'll get more points.

513
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:11,320
And this year's Best Researcher Award

514
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:12,480
will definitely be yours.

515
00:39:12,560 --> 00:39:14,240
Thank you so much, Boss.

516
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:40,840
Boss, the chairwoman is here.

517
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:44,880
Really? She didn't tell me.

518
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:47,160
Where's my grandma right now?

519
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:51,200
She's in Team B's research room with Song.

520
00:39:58,200 --> 00:39:59,200
Grandma.

521
00:39:59,760 --> 00:40:02,080
Not only did you help hide this,

522
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:04,240
you actually enabled her?

523
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:06,480
I guess so.

524
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:09,280
Because if you had stopped her,

525
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:11,920
I probably wouldn't have had to
come all the way here myself.

526
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:17,560
I never thought you'd be like this.

527
00:40:17,640 --> 00:40:19,600
<i>I'm truly disappointed in you.</i>

528
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:24,000
<i>What kind of older sister are you?</i>

529
00:40:24,680 --> 00:40:26,920
Look at this.
You let your sister get hurt like this.

530
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:28,680
You don't even take care of her.

531
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:30,000
This is unacceptable, Mudmee.

532
00:40:30,080 --> 00:40:31,800
You can't even do this right.

533
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:33,760
As the older sister,
it's your responsibility

534
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:35,440
to look after your sister's life.

535
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:36,880
You're so much older than her.

536
00:40:36,960 --> 00:40:38,720
I'm late.

537
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:40,280
What time is it?

538
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:41,880
Hello, Grandma.

539
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:44,880
- Mudmee, I'm leaving now.
- Piang, your skirt…

540
00:40:47,480 --> 00:40:49,280
The reason Piang is so stubborn

541
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:51,480
and refuses to listen
is partly because of you.

542
00:40:52,840 --> 00:40:54,200
What kind of a sister are you?

543
00:40:54,280 --> 00:40:56,120
You don't even know how to teach her.

544
00:40:56,200 --> 00:40:57,280
Useless.

545
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:42,720
Miss Kwanrin. You're still here?

546
00:41:43,520 --> 00:41:46,120
Or… did you forget something?

547
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:49,000
I forgot to take photos
of the finished work.

548
00:41:50,720 --> 00:41:51,680
Then go ahead.

549
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:50,880
Miss Kwanrin.

550
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:58,560
If… you don't have anywhere else to be,

551
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:02,440
could you stay with me for a while?

552
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:10,360
Sure.

553
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:25,080
- Tuna loin in soy.
- Tuna loin…

554
00:44:25,160 --> 00:44:27,920
- Soy, that's right.
- The slides are finished now, Song.

555
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:30,320
Can you check
if all the information is complete?

556
00:44:30,400 --> 00:44:31,360
Let me see.

557
00:44:32,120 --> 00:44:33,720
This one's okay.

558
00:44:33,800 --> 00:44:34,960
Correct.

559
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:37,240
I think that's all.

560
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:40,360
- Okay.
- Okay.

561
00:44:43,680 --> 00:44:44,680
Excellent.

562
00:44:47,400 --> 00:44:48,720
If this project gets approved,

563
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:50,600
we'll get extra points.

564
00:44:50,680 --> 00:44:54,160
And we'll send Song straight to
Mega Excellence.

565
00:44:54,240 --> 00:44:55,760
We'll get bigger bonuses too, right?

566
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:57,920
Yes, I've been waiting for this.

567
00:44:58,000 --> 00:44:59,680
If I get a bigger bonus this year,

568
00:44:59,760 --> 00:45:03,600
I'm taking the money overseas
and spoiling myself to the fullest.

569
00:45:03,680 --> 00:45:04,840
Maybe hit a host bar too.

570
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:06,920
Host bar, here I come.

571
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:09,640
- Nampraw.
- As for me,

572
00:45:09,720 --> 00:45:11,640
I'm buying a new phone.

573
00:45:11,720 --> 00:45:13,920
- This one is dying.
- True.

574
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:15,840
What about you, Song?

575
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:19,000
Me? Probably buying snacks for Moo Grob.

576
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:21,880
A new cat tree, new litter,
and a new fountain.

577
00:45:23,680 --> 00:45:26,400
- Such a cat person.
- A total cat lover. Meow.

578
00:45:26,480 --> 00:45:29,120
- Did that sound like a cat? Was it close?
- Yes.

579
00:45:31,080 --> 00:45:32,400
Ready, Song?

580
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:34,840
Ready, Boss.

581
00:45:36,280 --> 00:45:37,600
Focus, okay?

582
00:45:37,680 --> 00:45:39,840
Because your source of motivation
isn't here today.

583
00:45:40,800 --> 00:45:42,440
She's on a date by Grandma's orders.

584
00:45:43,240 --> 00:45:45,280
- Damn.
- Damn.

585
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:47,880
It's nothing, Boss.

586
00:45:53,880 --> 00:45:55,520
Namking was born on a Saturday,

587
00:45:55,600 --> 00:45:56,720
Year of the Goat, right?

588
00:45:56,800 --> 00:45:58,760
Our fortunes aren't compatible.

589
00:45:58,840 --> 00:46:01,400
You could say…
we're bad luck for each other.

590
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:03,280
If the two of us date,

591
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:05,600
it'll destroy both of our grandmas.

592
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:06,920
That's my final answer.

593
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:08,920
Namking, you're so cute.

594
00:46:09,000 --> 00:46:11,240
Who are you? Get out.

595
00:46:11,920 --> 00:46:13,200
I'm messy like this.

596
00:46:13,280 --> 00:46:15,960
You probably can't handle it, right?

597
00:46:16,040 --> 00:46:17,320
Want a taste?

598
00:46:17,400 --> 00:46:19,120
What year is this?

599
00:46:19,200 --> 00:46:22,320
Are we really supposed to be okay
with arranged dates?

600
00:46:22,400 --> 00:46:23,440
I refuse.

601
00:46:23,520 --> 00:46:25,200
I protest. I protest.

602
00:46:25,280 --> 00:46:27,000
Protest, protest, protest.

603
00:46:27,080 --> 00:46:27,920
- I'm protesting.
- Miss Piangrawin.

604
00:46:35,320 --> 00:46:36,680
Yes?

605
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:40,000
Dr. Namking asked me to let you know
she can't make it after all.

606
00:46:40,080 --> 00:46:42,800
An emergency case came up,
so she apologizes.

607
00:46:44,200 --> 00:46:45,600
That's completely fine.

608
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:49,200
Please tell her to hang in there.

609
00:46:49,280 --> 00:46:51,560
Okay, I'll excuse myself now.

610
00:46:52,640 --> 00:46:53,640
Yes.

611
00:47:12,240 --> 00:47:13,640
<i>Focus, okay?</i>

612
00:47:13,720 --> 00:47:16,320
Because your source of motivation
isn't here today.

613
00:47:17,160 --> 00:47:18,840
She's on a date by Grandma's orders.

614
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:31,720
Withdraw from this project.

615
00:47:34,680 --> 00:47:35,760
What?

616
00:47:37,640 --> 00:47:39,720
You're really just saying
that out of nowhere?

617
00:47:42,160 --> 00:47:45,600
You wouldn't want
your relationship with Piangrawin

618
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:48,080
to become gossip
around the company, right?

619
00:47:49,160 --> 00:47:52,400
So this was your doing. Go ahead then.

620
00:47:53,320 --> 00:47:56,160
Do whatever you want.
I have nothing left to lose anyway.

621
00:47:57,760 --> 00:48:01,160
Maybe you don't. But what about Piang?

622
00:48:01,960 --> 00:48:05,920
I have all the evidence.
Photos, audio clips, everything.

623
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:07,760
Just imagine

624
00:48:07,840 --> 00:48:10,720
how everyone in this company
would look at Piang?

625
00:48:10,800 --> 00:48:14,480
The president's granddaughter
running after a food researcher for love.

626
00:48:16,240 --> 00:48:19,040
It's pathetic. Don't you think?

627
00:48:35,800 --> 00:48:36,720
<i>Everyone,</i>

628
00:48:36,800 --> 00:48:40,480
this is a project that 126 Food
is extremely confident in.

629
00:48:40,560 --> 00:48:44,080
Now please welcome Song Sadanun,
the owner of this project,

630
00:48:44,160 --> 00:48:45,480
to present it for us.

631
00:48:46,800 --> 00:48:49,360
Good luck. Go for it.

632
00:48:59,320 --> 00:49:00,680
Song.

633
00:49:02,960 --> 00:49:05,080
What's wrong? Go on.

634
00:49:08,200 --> 00:49:09,120
What's happening?

635
00:49:10,600 --> 00:49:11,800
I don't know either.

636
00:49:18,800 --> 00:49:20,960
I sincerely apologize, everyone.

637
00:49:21,040 --> 00:49:23,320
I won't be able to present this project.

638
00:49:27,680 --> 00:49:30,720
What's wrong? Is something wrong?

639
00:49:41,200 --> 00:49:43,600
There seems to be
an issue with the formula.

640
00:49:44,160 --> 00:49:47,680
We only discovered it a few minutes
before entering the meeting room.

641
00:49:48,560 --> 00:49:52,440
I sincerely apologize to everyone
for wasting your time.

642
00:49:55,840 --> 00:49:58,400
But we checked everything. It was correct.

643
00:50:01,280 --> 00:50:02,680
Hey.

644
00:50:02,760 --> 00:50:05,320
- It was correct.
- What the hell is wrong with her?

645
00:50:13,440 --> 00:50:14,720
Song.

646
00:50:23,640 --> 00:50:25,520
Wait, Song.

647
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:27,440
What happened? Why did you suddenly--

648
00:50:27,520 --> 00:50:29,200
Just leave me alone already.

649
00:51:31,000 --> 00:51:33,080
- He came looking for you?
- How did he get here?

650
00:51:34,440 --> 00:51:35,920
For this competition.

651
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:37,760
No one is allowed to withdraw.

652
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:40,360
You look at your own granddaughter

653
00:51:40,440 --> 00:51:41,920
as nothing more than a business tool.

654
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:43,360
<i>You paired them up.</i>

655
00:51:43,440 --> 00:51:46,320
<i>For your own benefit.</i>
<i>I can't believe that nowadays,</i>

656
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:48,720
<i>there are still people</i>
<i>who think like this.</i>

657
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:51,440
Sometimes I think being the bad guy,

658
00:51:51,520 --> 00:51:53,240
actually makes life easier.

659
00:51:54,360 --> 00:51:55,600
<i>If you want to see her.</i>

660
00:51:55,680 --> 00:51:56,640
<i>You need an excuse.</i>

661
00:51:56,720 --> 00:51:58,520
<i>Like being friends with benefits.</i>

662
00:51:58,600 --> 00:52:01,200
<i>A relationship where two people meet up.</i>

663
00:52:01,280 --> 00:52:02,960
<i>Just to have sex.</i>
